gurmukhi: ਬੇਦ ਬਿਰੰਚਿ ਬਿਚਾਰੁ ਨ ਪਾਵਤ ਚਕ੍ਰਿਤ ਸੇਖ ਸਿਵਾਦਿ ਭੲੇ ਹੈ
transliteration: Bayd Biranchi Bichaaru N Paavata , Chakrit Saykh Sivaadi Bhaay Hai ?
translation: Brahma studied and reflected on the Vedas yet could not fathom the beginning and the end of the infinite Lord. Sheshnag, with his thousand tongues and Shiv Ji are falling into ecstatic state singing His paeans and contemplating on His extent.

gurmukhi: ਜੋਗ ਸਮਾਧਿ ਅਰਾਧਤ ਨਾਰਦ ਸਾਰਦ ਸੁਕ੍ਰ ਸਨਾਤ ਨੲੇ ਹੈ
transliteration: Jog Samaadhi Araadhat Naarada , Saarad Soukr Sanaat Naay Hai ?
translation: Sage Narad, goddess Saraswati, Shukracharya and Sanatan the sons of Brahma are bowing before Him after contemplating on Him in meditation.

gurmukhi: ਅਾਦਿ ਅਨਾਦਿ ਅਗਾਦਿ ਅਗੋਚਰ ਨਾਮ ਨਿਰੰਜਨ ਜਾਪ ਜੲੇ ਹੈ
transliteration: Aadi Anaadi Agaadi Agochara , Naam Niranjan Jaap Jaay Hai ?
translation: The Lord who is since the beginning of the beginning, is beyond the beginning is spread beyond the comprehension of mind and senses. Such mammonless and blemishless Lord is being meditated upon by all.

gurmukhi: ਸ੍ਰੀ ਗੁਰਦੇਵ ਸੁਮੇਵ ਸੁਸੰਗਤਿ ਪੈਰੀ ਪੲੇ ਭਾੲੀ ਪੈਰੀ ਪੲੇ ਹੈ ||੫੫੪||
transliteration: Sree Gurdayv Soumayv Sousangati , Pairee Paay Bhaaee Pairee Paay Hai ?554?
translation: The True Guru who is engrossed in such God is absorbed and permeated in the congregation of supreme people. 0 brother! I fall, yes I fall on the holy feet of such a True Guru.  (554)
